Class ExpectedResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • hypeerweb.SimplifiedNodeDomain
      • testing.ExpectedResult

  • public class ExpectedResult
extends SimplifiedNodeDomain
    Given integer values for the hyPeerWebSize and the webId we can compute integer values representing the height, neighbors, upPointers, downPointers, fold, surrogateFold, inverseSurrogateFold, and state of a node. The constructor for this class does just that representing the result as a SimplifiedNodeDomain. 
     Domain:
     Inherited from SimplifiedNodeDomain

    Scott

    • Constructor Detail

      • ExpectedResult

        public ExpectedResult(int hyPeerWebSize,
              int webId)
        Constructs an SimplifiedNodeDomain representation of the expected webId, neighbors, upPointers, downPointers, fold, surrogateFold, inverseSurrogateFold, and state of a node given integer values for the hyPeerWebSize and webId value.
        Parameters:
        hyPeerWebSize - the number of nodes in the hypothetical hyPeerWeb
        webId - the value of the webId for a hypothetical node in the hyPeerWeb
        Precondition:
        hyPeerWebSize >= 1 AND 0 <= webId < hyPeerWebSize
        Postcondition:
        this.webId = webId AND
        height = the expected height of this hypothetical node AND
        neighbors = a hash set of integers representing all the neighbors of the hypothetical node AND
        upPointers = a hash set of integers representing all the upPointers of the hypothetical node AND
        downPointers = a hash set of integers representing all the downPointers of the hypothetical node AND
        fold = expected integer value of the webId for the fold AND
        surrogateFold = expected integer value of the webId for the surrogateFold AND
        inverseSurrogateFold = expected integer value of the webId of the surrogateFold AND
        state = expected state's STATE_ID

    • Method Detail

      • locationOfHighestOneBit

        public int locationOfHighestOneBit(int id)
        Returns the location of the most significant one bit in the given id.
        Parameters:
        id - the id we are going to examine.
        Precondition:
        id >= 0
        Postcondition:
        id.binaryRepresentation[result] = 1 AND ∀ result <= i < 32 (id.binaryRepresentation[i] = 0)
